---
name: scljet-sql-group-by
description: SclJet SQL GROUP BY — per-group aggregates, one row per group (matches reference sqlite3)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL GROUP BY

`SELECT col, AGG(col2) FROM t [WHERE …] GROUP BY col` partitions the WHERE-filtered rows by the
group key (rows sorted by the key, then consecutive runs), computes each aggregate per group, and
emits one row per group (groups in key order). Every result is byte-identical to reference sqlite3
running the same SQL on the same file (verified out-of-band); locked here across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def run(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(id INTEGER, dept TEXT, age INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("eng"), SqlInteger(30L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("sales"), SqlInteger(40L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("eng"), SqlInteger(25L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("hr"), SqlInteger(50L)),
       List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("sales"), SqlInteger(35L)),
       List(SqlInteger(6L), SqlText("eng"), SqlInteger(45L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    run(db, "SELECT dept, COUNT(*) FROM t GROUP BY dept")
    run(db, "SELECT dept, COUNT(*), SUM(age), MIN(age), MAX(age) FROM t GROUP BY dept")
    run(db, "SELECT dept, COUNT(*) FROM t WHERE age > 30 GROUP BY dept")
    run(db, "SELECT dept FROM t GROUP BY dept")
    run(db, "SELECT age, COUNT(*) FROM t GROUP BY age")
    run(db, "SELECT COUNT(*), MAX(age) FROM t")
```
